title: Dangers Of Testosterone Therapy | 10 News+
description: There are fears of a 'masculinity crisis' for young Aussie men, who are being increasingly bombarded by social media content about low testosterone. Influencers are peddling testing and treatments, with new research finding they're being normalised and shaping the identities of young men. 10 News+ is joined by Dr Brooke Nickel to discuss the best ways to keep teens healthy and avoid misinformation. title: Could Flat-Pack Homes Be The Solution To Australia's Housing Crisis? | 10 News+
description: Kit homes are emerging as a potential fix for Australia's housing crisis. title: Could Keir Starmer Be Sacked Over His US Ambassador’s Connection To Jeffrey Epstein? | 10 News+
description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer has apologised to Jeffrey Epstein’s victims after London police launched a criminal investigation this week into Starmer’s US Ambassador, Lord Peter Mandelson. It’s alleged that Mandelson shared sensitive information with Jeffrey Epstein in 2009 during his time as Business Minister. The PM says Lord Mandelson was asked directly about the nature of his relationship with Epstein before he was appointed as ambassador. "He portrayed Epstein as someone he barely knew,” Starmer said. title: Storm Leonardo Floods Spain And Portugal, Killing One And Leaving Woman Missing | 10 News
description: Torrential rain from Storm Leonardo has triggered deadly floods across southern Spain and Portugal, leaving one man dead and a woman missing.  Months’ worth of rain fell in hours, forcing nearly 4,000 evacuations, cutting roads and rail lines, and flooding towns in Andalusia and southern Portugal.  In Spain, a woman was swept away by a river while trying to save her dog, while in Portugal a driver died after his car was washed off a road near a dam.  Authorities warn more storms are coming, with scientists linking the intensifying weather to human-driven climate change.
